The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a new architecture for constructing deep CNNs, which involves optimizing the efficiency of network parameters, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed architecture on benchmark datasets, suggesting a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the discriminability of features for classification tasks, indicating a potential focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
